HEADWORD: Unlute
<hw>Un*lute"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>lute</ets>.]</ety> <def>To separate, as things
cemented or luted; to take the lute or the clay from.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

